members.name: getEyeHeight
members.comment: Gets the height of the living entity's eyes above its Location.

return: height of the living entity's eyes above its location

members.name: getEyeHeight
members.comment: Gets the height of the living entity's eyes above its Location.

param: ignorePose - if set to true, the effects of pose changes, eg sneaking and gliding will be ignored
return: height of the living entity's eyes above its location

members.name: getEyeLocation
members.comment: Get a Location detailing the current eye position of the living entity.

return: a location at the eyes of the living entity

members.name: getLineOfSight
members.comment: Gets all blocks along the living entity's line of sight. This list contains all blocks from the living entity's eye position to target inclusive. This method considers all blocks as 1x1x1 in size.

param: transparent - Set containing all transparent block Materials (set to null for only air)
maxDistance - this is the maximum distance to scan (may be limited by server by at least 100 blocks, no less)
return: list containing all blocks along the living entity's line of sight

members.name: getTargetBlock
members.comment: Gets the block that the living entity has targeted. This method considers all blocks as 1x1x1 in size. To take exact block collision shapes into account, see getTargetBlockExact(int, FluidCollisionMode).

param: transparent - Set containing all transparent block Materials (set to null for only air)
maxDistance - this is the maximum distance to scan (may be limited by server by at least 100 blocks, no less)
return: block that the living entity has targeted

members.name: getLastTwoTargetBlocks
members.comment: Gets the last two blocks along the living entity's line of sight. The target block will be the last block in the list. This method considers all blocks as 1x1x1 in size.

param: transparent - Set containing all transparent block Materials (set to null for only air)
maxDistance - this is the maximum distance to scan. This may be further limited by the server, but never to less than 100 blocks
return: list containing the last 2 blocks along the living entity's line of sight

members.name: getTargetBlockExact
members.comment: Gets the block that the living entity has targeted. This takes the blocks' precise collision shapes into account. Fluids are ignored. This may cause loading of chunks! Some implementations may impose artificial restrictions on the maximum distance.

return: block that the living entity has targeted

members.name: getTargetBlockExact
members.comment: Gets the block that the living entity has targeted. This takes the blocks' precise collision shapes into account. This may cause loading of chunks! Some implementations may impose artificial restrictions on the maximum distance.

return: block that the living entity has targeted

members.name: rayTraceBlocks
members.comment: Performs a ray trace that provides information on the targeted block. This takes the blocks' precise collision shapes into account. Fluids are ignored. This may cause loading of chunks! Some implementations may impose artificial restrictions on the maximum distance.

return: information on the targeted block, or null if there is no targeted block in range

members.name: rayTraceBlocks
members.comment: Performs a ray trace that provides information on the targeted block. This takes the blocks' precise collision shapes into account. This may cause loading of chunks! Some implementations may impose artificial restrictions on the maximum distance.

return: information on the targeted block, or null if there is no targeted block in range

members.name: getRemainingAir
members.comment: Returns the amount of air that the living entity has remaining, in ticks.

return: amount of air remaining

members.name: setRemainingAir
members.comment: Sets the amount of air that the living entity has remaining, in ticks.

members.name: getMaximumAir
members.comment: Returns the maximum amount of air the living entity can have, in ticks.

return: maximum amount of air

members.name: setMaximumAir
members.comment: Sets the maximum amount of air the living entity can have, in ticks.

members.name: getArrowCooldown
members.comment: Gets the time in ticks until the next arrow leaves the entity's body.

return: ticks until arrow leaves

members.name: setArrowCooldown
members.comment: Sets the time in ticks until the next arrow leaves the entity's body.

members.name: getArrowsInBody
members.comment: Gets the amount of arrows in an entity's body.

return: amount of arrows in body

members.name: setArrowsInBody
members.comment: Set the amount of arrows in the entity's body.

param: count - amount of arrows in entity's body

members.name: getMaximumNoDamageTicks
members.comment: Returns the living entity's current maximum no damage ticks. This is the maximum duration in which the living entity will not take damage.

return: maximum no damage ticks

members.name: setMaximumNoDamageTicks
members.comment: Sets the living entity's current maximum no damage ticks.

param: ticks - maximum amount of no damage ticks

members.name: getLastDamage
members.comment: Returns the living entity's last damage taken in the current no damage ticks time. Only damage higher than this amount will further damage the living entity.

return: damage taken since the last no damage ticks time period

members.name: setLastDamage
members.comment: Sets the damage dealt within the current no damage ticks time period.

members.name: getNoDamageTicks
members.comment: Returns the living entity's current no damage ticks.

return: amount of no damage ticks

members.name: setNoDamageTicks
members.comment: Sets the living entity's current no damage ticks.

members.name: getKiller
members.comment: Gets the player identified as the killer of the living entity. May be null.

return: killer player, or null if none found

members.name: addPotionEffect
members.comment: Adds the given PotionEffect to the living entity.

return: whether the effect could be added

members.name: addPotionEffect
members.comment: Adds the given PotionEffect to the living entity. Only one potion effect can be present for a given PotionEffectType.

param: force - whether conflicting effects should be removed
return: whether the effect could be added

members.name: addPotionEffects
members.comment: Attempts to add all of the given PotionEffect to the living entity.

return: whether all of the effects could be added

members.name: hasPotionEffect
members.comment: Returns whether the living entity already has an existing effect of the given PotionEffectType applied to it.

return: whether the living entity has this potion effect active on them

members.name: getPotionEffect
members.comment: Returns the active PotionEffect of the specified type. If the effect is not present on the entity then null will be returned.

return: the effect active on this entity, or null if not active.

members.name: removePotionEffect
members.comment: Removes any effects present of the given PotionEffectType.

members.name: getActivePotionEffects
members.comment: Returns all currently active PotionEffects on the living entity.

return: a collection of PotionEffects

members.name: hasLineOfSight
members.comment: Checks whether the living entity has block line of sight to another. This uses the same algorithm that hostile mobs use to find the closest player.

param: other - the entity to determine line of sight to
return: true if there is a line of sight, false if not

members.name: getRemoveWhenFarAway
members.comment: Returns if the living entity despawns when away from players or not. By default, animals are not removed while other mobs are.

return: true if the living entity is removed when away from players

members.name: setRemoveWhenFarAway
members.comment: Sets whether or not the living entity despawns when away from players or not.

members.name: getEquipment
members.comment: Gets the inventory with the equipment worn by the living entity.

return: the living entity's inventory

members.name: setCanPickupItems
members.comment: Sets whether or not the living entity can pick up items.

param: pickup - whether or not the living entity can pick up items

members.name: getCanPickupItems
members.comment: Gets if the living entity can pick up items.

return: whether or not the living entity can pick up items

members.name: isLeashed
members.comment: Returns whether the entity is currently leashed.

return: whether the entity is leashed

members.name: getLeashHolder
members.comment: Gets the entity that is currently leading this entity.

throws: IllegalStateException - if not currently leashed
return: the entity holding the leash

members.name: setLeashHolder
members.comment: Sets the leash on this entity to be held by the supplied entity. This method has no effect on EnderDragons, Withers, Players, or Bats. Non-living entities excluding leashes will not persist as leash holders.

param: holder - the entity to leash this entity to, or null to unleash
return: whether the operation was successful

members.name: isGliding
members.comment: Checks to see if an entity is gliding, such as using an Elytra.

return: True if this entity is gliding.

members.name: setGliding
members.comment: Makes entity start or stop gliding. This will work even if an Elytra is not equipped, but will be reverted by the server immediately after unless an event-cancelling mechanism is put in place.

param: gliding - True if the entity is gliding.

members.name: isSwimming
members.comment: Checks to see if an entity is swimming.

return: True if this entity is swimming.

members.name: setSwimming
members.comment: Makes entity start or stop swimming. This may have unexpected results if the entity is not in water.

param: swimming - True if the entity is swimming.

members.name: isRiptiding
members.comment: Checks to see if an entity is currently using the Riptide enchantment.

return: True if this entity is currently riptiding.

members.name: isSleeping
members.comment: Returns whether this entity is slumbering.

return: slumber state

members.name: isClimbing
members.comment: Gets if the entity is climbing.

return: if the entity is climbing

members.name: setAI
members.comment: Sets whether an entity will have AI. The entity will be completely unable to move if it has no AI.

param: ai - whether the mob will have AI or not.

members.name: hasAI
members.comment: Checks whether an entity has AI. The entity will be completely unable to move if it has no AI.

return: true if the entity has AI, otherwise false.

members.name: attack
members.comment: Makes this entity attack the given entity with a melee attack. Attack damage is calculated by the server from the attributes and equipment of this mob, and knockback is applied to target as appropriate.

members.name: swingMainHand
members.comment: Makes this entity swing their main hand. This method does nothing if this entity does not have an animation for swinging their main hand.

members.name: swingOffHand
members.comment: Makes this entity swing their off hand. This method does nothing if this entity does not have an animation for swinging their off hand.

members.name: setCollidable
members.comment: Set if this entity will be subject to collisions with other entities. Exemptions to this rule can be managed with getCollidableExemptions()

members.name: isCollidable
members.comment: Gets if this entity is subject to collisions with other entities. Some entities might be exempted from the collidable rule of this entity. Use getCollidableExemptions() to get these. Please note that this method returns only the custom collidable state, not whether the entity is non-collidable for other reasons such as being dead.

return: collision status

members.name: getCollidableExemptions
members.comment: Gets a mutable set of UUIDs of the entities which are exempt from the entity's collidable rule and which's collision with this entity will behave the opposite of it. This set can be modified to add or remove exemptions. For example if collidable is true and an entity is in the exemptions set then it will not collide with it. Similarly if collidable is false and an entity is in this set then it will still collide with it. Note these exemptions are not (currently) persistent.

return: the collidable exemption set

members.name: getMemory
members.comment: Returns the value of the memory specified. Note that the value is null when the specific entity does not have that value by default.

Type Parameters:: T - the type of the return value
return: a instance of the memory section value or null if not present

members.name: setMemory
members.comment: Sets the value of the memory specified. Note that the value will not be persisted when the specific entity does not have that value by default.

Type Parameters:: T - the type of the passed value

members.name: getCategory
members.comment: Get the category to which this entity belongs. Categories may subject this entity to additional effects, benefits or debuffs.

return: the entity category

members.name: setInvisible
members.comment: Sets whether the entity is invisible or not.

members.name: isInvisible
members.comment: Gets whether the entity is invisible or not.

return: Whether the entity is invisible
